flowRoot.flowPara: App menu
Contact menu
Goals
* Adopt GNOME 3 application design patterns where possible
* Work well when maximised
* Enable person-centric activity syndication
* Avoid interface depth
* Simplify contact editing process
* Provide a quick and easy way to initiate conversations
The current letter and the selected contact should always be visible in the list - they should stick to the top of the list when scrolling

Selecting a message, document or photo opens it in the relevant application

Recent status messages are displayed below the contact name; these act as links
Image title and source are displayed in a tooltip on hover
Non-editable details display their origin
